Class SimpleOrderQueue<T,E extends Order>

  • Object
    • SimpleOrderQueue<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type: the dispatchable threshold type
    E - Elements: the type of order(s) to be contained within the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    OrderQueue<T,E>

    public final class SimpleOrderQueue<T,E extends Order>
extends Object
implements OrderQueue<T,E>
    A simple OrderQueue implementation which stores orders in a TreeSet.

    AndrewStefanich
    See Also:

      • dequeue

        public E dequeue()
        Removes the highest dispatchable order in the queue. If there are orders, but they do not meet dispatch criteria, the order is not removed and null is returned.
        Specified by:
        dequeue in interface OrderQueue<T,E extends Order>
        Returns:
        the first dispatchable order in the queue; null if there are no dispatchable orders in the queue.

      • dispatchOrders

        public void dispatchOrders()
        Executes the callback for each dispatchable order. Each dispatchable order is removed from the queue and passed to the callback. If there is no callback/orderprocessor registered, the order is simply revmoed from the queue.
        Specified by:
        dispatchOrders in interface OrderQueue<T,E extends Order>
